* china's economy grew by 2so fast as western economies for many years; does that show that communism can be economically efficient or even superior? no;
* the communism of modern china is very different from the communism of around 1960; the chinese state eased the economic restrictions on private economical activities by much; in some respect it is more free now than in western countries; for example consumer and worker "protection" may be less, the patent system is probably smaller, private data protection is probably less, ...;
* the chinese state [i guess] spends relatively less on social gifts and more on investments, like infrastructure, buildings, foreign state bonds, ...; relatively high social gifting in democracies is not part of their capitalism, but the opposite
